recommended for The crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root intiation : 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage : 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage : 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage : 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

Recommended  for The crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root intiation : 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage : 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage : 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage : 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

KCCAns:
Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

KCCAns: Usually, during the rainy season the need for irrigation of mung beans does not require irrigation. However, during this period, due to a long period of rainfall after one year or a shortage of moisture, a light irrigation is necessary when the beans are formed. In the spring and summer, irrigation is required for 10-15 days intervals. Irrigation should be stopped 15 days before harvesting. If there is excess rain in the rainy season or the water is filled with water, then the extra water should be removed from the field, which keeps the air communication in the soil.

Pusa Kesar

This is the type of red carrot's best carrot. The leaves are small and the roots are long, attractive red color is central part and narrow. Crop is ready in 90-110 days. Production: 300-350 quintals per hectare.

Pusa

Meghali: It is a hybrid species of orange pulp, small top and carotene. Aged sowing can be sown till August-September till sowing. Seeds are produced in the field. The crop is ready in 100-110 days of planting, the yield is 250-300 quintals per hectare.

Pusa Yamdagni

This species has been developed by IKRI Regional Center Katrine. It yields 150-200 quintals per hectare.

Nantes

This type of thread is of cylindrical silvery color. The central part inside the root is soft, sweet and fragrant. Prepares in 110-112 days. The yield is 100-125 quintals per hectare.
